cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on the application of deep learning in computer vision, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also discusses the importance of large datasets and the use of pre-training, which are topics commonly associated with the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions object detection, semantic segmentation, and human pose estimation, which are tasks related to natural language processing and multimedia, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-categories.
